Description: The series revolves around three preadolescent boys: Ed, who is slow-witted and often speaks in non sequiturs; Edd, usually called "Double D", who is rather intelligent and polite, if high-strung; and Eddy, who is the avaricious &#039;leader&#039; of the trio. Collectively known as "the Eds," the three hang around in a suburban cul-de-sac. Led by Eddy, the Eds scheme to make money off their peers, but their plans usually fail, leaving them in various predicaments. The number of characters in Ed, Edd n Eddy is fixed at twelve. No other characters have appeared besides the main cast and adults are never seen. There is no given timeline for the show; Danny Antonucci has stated that he wanted the show to appeal to any generation. Therefore, if a VCR or computer is needed in a plot, it is there.

[BloodLogic Note: The great part about this show is that they have an episode where the workers go on strike, and it expresses the evolution of those socio-economic relationships in a rather sophisticated way -- compared to, say, the Ninja Turtles. And those are ideas we want to express to our kids as early as possible. They need to grow up knowing that the only way they can achieve what they individually seek, their liberty and fair share of the fruits of their labors, is by acting collectively. All power to the syndicates!]
